.TH "lpfc_reset_barrier" 9 "lpfc_reset_barrier" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_reset_barrier \- Make HBA ready for HBA reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lpfc_reset_barrier
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
Pointer to HBA context object.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called before resetting an HBA. This function is called
with hbalock held and requests HBA to quiesce DMAs before a reset.
